title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 6
text:
What channel is Kansas City Royals-Toronto Blue Jays on? TV, live stream for ALCS Game 6 Marco Estrada Toronto Blue Jays' closer Roberto Osuna celebrates with catcher Dioner Navarro after their 7-1 win over the Kansas City Royals in Game 5 of the American League Championship Series on Wednesday in Toronto. (Nathan Denette | The Associated Press) Comments 
The Toronto Blue Jays delayed their elimination with a win over Kansas City on Wednesday and now their American League Championship Series shifts to Kauffman Stadium for Game 6 tonight. 
The Royals, trying to reach their second straight World Series, lead the best-of-7 series three games to two. 
David Price will start on the mound for Toronto against Kansas City's Yordano Ventura. 
The game starts at 8 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1. 
Here's how to view Fox Sports 1 in Central New York: Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) 
You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
